etsysMgmdExtMIB.name: etsysMgmdExtMIB

revisions.description: Added etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitEnable and etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitTime leafs to the config area.
Added new counters to the StatsCntrs table.
The initial version of this MIB module

etsysMgmdExtMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 9 Northeastern Blvd. Salem, NH 03079 USA Phone: +1 603 952 5000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsysMgmdExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP MIB under the Enterasys Networks enterprise OID pertaining to IGMP operation on a device. This MIB contains Enterasys proprietary MGMD information that goes above and beyond any IETF multicast MIBs. It is intended to cover any Enterasys value added features and configurations.

MGMDNumGroupsTc.name: MGMDNumGroupsTc
MGMDNumGroupsTc.description: This textual convention describes the available MGMD number of groups size selection. None means no flows are currently supported. The rest of the settings are dependent on which hardware platform you are running on. Please see the users manual for your device to see what these values mean.

MGMDPortModeTc.name: MGMDPortModeTc
MGMDPortModeTc.description: This textual convention maps out possible MGMD port modes.

MGMDDiscoveredRouterModeTc.name: MGMDDiscoveredRouterModeTc
MGMDDiscoveredRouterModeTc.description: This textual convention maps the possible ways a router may be discovered by the device.

MGMDProtocolClassTc.name: MGMDProtocolClassTc
MGMDProtocolClassTc.description: This textual convention describes the possible ways IGMP/MLD can classify received frames.

MGMDProtocolIdTc.name: MGMDProtocolIdTc
MGMDProtocolIdTc.description: Bit definitions for each of the IP protocol numbers assigned by IANA.

MGMDInputFilterFlowActionsTc.name: MGMDInputFilterFlowActionsTc
MGMDInputFilterFlowActionsTc.description: This textual convention describes the possible actions an IGMP/MLD input filter may take for flows. Please see the users manual for your device to see what these values mean.

MGMDInputFilterProtocolActionsTc.name: MGMDInputFilterProtocolActionsTc
MGMDInputFilterProtocolActionsTc.description: This textual convention describes the possible actions an IGMP/MLD input filter may take for protocols. Please see the users manual for your device to see what these values mean.

etsysMgmdExtConfigRevString.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigRevString
etsysMgmdExtConfigRevString.description: This object is a textual representation of the revision of the Enterasys MGMD MIB in the firmware.

etsysMgmdExtConfigFullAction.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigFullAction
etsysMgmdExtConfigFullAction.description: This object defines the behavior of IGMP/MLD when its group table is full. The user may choose to send multicast frames to known routers, or flood these frames to the vlan.

etsysMgmdExtConfigMinNumberOfGroups.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigMinNumberOfGroups
etsysMgmdExtConfigMinNumberOfGroups.description: This object will state the minimum number of multicast groups this device is capable of setting.

etsysMgmdExtConfigDefaultNumberOfGroups.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigDefaultNumberOfGroups
etsysMgmdExtConfigDefaultNumberOfGroups.description: This object states the default number of multicast groups this device will be set to.

etsysMgmdExtConfigMaxNumberOfGroups.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigMaxNumberOfGroups
etsysMgmdExtConfigMaxNumberOfGroups.description: This object states the maximum number of multicast groups this device is capable of setting.

etsysMgmdExtConfigNumberOfGroups.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigNumberOfGroups
etsysMgmdExtConfigNumberOfGroups.description: This object allow the user to select the IGMP/MLD group table size for this device.

etsysMgmdExtConfigUnknownInputAction.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigUnknownInputAction
etsysMgmdExtConfigUnknownInputAction.description: This object defines the behavior of the first 'x' frames of an unknown multicast flow when no clients are present. The user may choose to follow the IGMP/MLD specification and discard the frames, send these frame to multicast routers, or flood these frames to the vlan.

etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitEnable.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitEnable
etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitEnable.description: This object enables or disables a feature whereby any flow received will be delayed in hardware programming for the number of 10ms intervals defined in etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitTime.

etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitTime.name: etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitTime
etsysMgmdExtConfigFlowWaitTime.description: The number of 10ms blocks to wait before allowing hardware flow setup.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceTable.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceTable
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the interfaces on which IGMP/MLD is enabled.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceEntry
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an interface on which IGMP/MLD is enabled.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceApplication.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceApplication
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceApplication.description: The multicast application this object refers to. ipv4(1) refers to IGMP, ipv6(2) refers to MLD.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceQueryEnableState.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceQueryEnableState
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceQueryEnableState.description: The state of active querying on this interface.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFastLeaveState.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFastLeaveState
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFastLeaveState.description: The state of Fast Leave on this interface.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceClearGroups.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceClearGroups
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceClearGroups.description: A mechanism to flush the database of IP group members maintained by the IGMP snooping application on this interface. Setting the value to true will clear the group members. Setting the value to false will have no effect. This value will always read false

etsysMgmdExtRtrAlertRequired.name: etsysMgmdExtRtrAlertRequired
etsysMgmdExtRtrAlertRequired.reference: RFC 2236, sections 2 and 10. RFC 3376, sections 4 and 9.
etsysMgmdExtRtrAlertRequired.description: A mechanism to allow backward compatibility with older implementations of IGMPv2 that may be present on this interface. The default setting of this value to true will cause IGMPv2 messages missing the router alert IP option to be discarded. Setting this value to false will cause the router alert requirement for IGMPv2 messages heard on this interface to be ignored.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterId.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterId
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterId.description: The IGMP/MLD input filter from etsysMgmdExtInputFilterGroup, to apply to this interface. This will apply the given input filter to all input on this interface.

etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterIdEnable.name: etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterIdEnable
etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterIdEnable.description: Enable or disable the filter id set in etsysMgmdExtInterfaceFilterId.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheTable.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheTable
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the static IGMP/MLD cache entries.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheEntry
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a static entry that IGMP/MLD will act upon.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheIPAddrType.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheIPAddrType
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheIPAddrType.description: The IP address type of the group and source IPs.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheGroupIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheGroupIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheGroupIPAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for IGMP to send multicast data to.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheSourceIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheSourceIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheSourceIPAddress.description: The IP source address of this entry. For IGMP Version 2, and MLD v1, use the unspecified address.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheIncludeList.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheIncludeList
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheIncludeList.description: The set of ports configured by management for this multicast group and this interface to which multicast group-addressed data frames are to be forwarded. The default is all bits cleared.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheExcludeList.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheExcludeList
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheExcludeList.description: The set of ports configured by management for this multicast group and this interface for which multicast group-addressed data frames are not to be forwarded. The default is all bits cleared.

etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheRowStatus.name: etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheRowStatus
etsysMgmdExtStaticCacheRowStatus.description: active(1) creates a static entry. notInService(2) disables a static entry. destroy(6) deletes a static entry.

etsysMgmdExtCacheTable.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheTable
etsysMgmdExtCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for interfaces with members on this particular interface. This table provides a version 3 capable etsysMgmdExtCacheTable, with a bridge PortList leaf vs mib2 interface index.

etsysMgmdExtCacheEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheEntry
etsysMgmdExtCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysMgmdExtCacheTable.

etsysMgmdExtCacheIPAddrType.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheIPAddrType
etsysMgmdExtCacheIPAddrType.description: The IP address type of the group and source IP addresses.

etsysMgmdExtCacheGroupIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheGroupIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtCacheGroupIPAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for this entry.

etsysMgmdExtCacheSourceIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheSourceIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtCacheSourceIPAddress.description: The IP source address of this entry.

etsysMgmdExtCacheExpiryTime.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheExpiryTime
etsysMgmdExtCacheExpiryTime.description: The time in seconds this entry will expire in.

etsysMgmdExtCacheIncludePortList.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheIncludePortList
etsysMgmdExtCacheIncludePortList.description: The set of bridge ports for this multicast group, interface, and source IP address where the entry filter-mode is include.

etsysMgmdExtCacheExcludePortList.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheExcludePortList
etsysMgmdExtCacheExcludePortList.description: The set of bridge ports for this multicast group, interface, and source IP address where the entry filter-mode is exclude.

etsysMgmdExtCacheSrcPort.name: etsysMgmdExtCacheSrcPort
etsysMgmdExtCacheSrcPort.description: The source bridge port of the multicast data stream if available.

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterTable.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterTable
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the routers seen on particular ports of a VLAN through either protocol snooping or ICMP Router Discovery.

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterEntry
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterEntry.description: An entry representing the routers seen on particular ports on a given interface index.

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterApplication.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterApplication
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterApplication.description: The application these objects refer to, ipv4(1) - IGMP, ipv6(2) - MLD.

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterLearnedMetho.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterLearnedMethod
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterLearnedMetho.description: The method this router was learned by.

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterEgressing.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterEgressing
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterEgressing.description: Indicates if this bridge port is egressing out this interface.

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterStaticPortLi.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterStaticPortList
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterStaticPortLi.description: Indicates if this bridge port on this interface is static. This leaf is OPTIONAL

etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterBridgePortAg.name: etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterBridgePortAgeTime
etsysMgmdExtDiscoveredRouterBridgePortAg.description: The time in ticks from the last received protocol packet, until this bridge port will age out.

etsysMgmdExtPortTable.name: etsysMgmdExtPortTable
etsysMgmdExtPortTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing a bridge port's bindings to multicast group IP addresses, interface ids, and source IP addresses.

etsysMgmdExtPortTableEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtPortTableEntry
etsysMgmdExtPortTableEntry.description: An entry representing the binding of bridge port to multicast group IP address, interface, and source IP address.

etsysMgmdExtPortMode.name: etsysMgmdExtPortMode
etsysMgmdExtPortMode.description: The mode of the given bridge port.

etsysMgmdExtPortIPAddressType.name: etsysMgmdExtPortIPAddressType
etsysMgmdExtPortIPAddressType.description: The type of group and source IP addresses.

etsysMgmdExtPortTableGroupIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtPortTableGroupIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtPortTableGroupIPAddress.description: The multicast group IP address bound to this port entry.

etsysMgmdExtPortTableSourceIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtPortTableSourceIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtPortTableSourceIPAddress.description: The IP source address bound to this port entry.

etsysMgmdExtPortTableExpireTime.name: etsysMgmdExtPortTableExpireTime
etsysMgmdExtPortTableExpireTime.description: The time in seconds from the last join received until that this port will expire.

etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveTable.name: etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveTable
etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing a bridge port's fast leave state.

etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveTableEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveTableEntry
etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveTableEntry.description: An entry representing the state of the fast leave function for the given bridge port.

etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveState.name: etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveState
etsysMgmdExtPortFastLeaveState.description: Enable or disable the fast leave function for the given bridge port.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsTable.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsTable
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing counters and statistics seen on the given multicast application.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsEntry
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsEntry.description: An entry representing the statistics and counters on the given application.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsApplication.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsApplication
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsApplication.description: The multicast application to get stats and counters for. ipv4(1) - IGMP, ipv6(2) - MLD.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsGroupFull.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsGroupFull
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsGroupFull.description: Flag to indicate if the group table is full(true) or not(false).

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesSent.description: The number of version 1 queries this device has sent out.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV2QueriesSent.description: The number of version 2 queries this device has sent out.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesSent.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesSent
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesSent.description: The number of version 3 queries this device has sent out. This will read 0 for MLD.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesSent.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesSent
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesSent.description: The number of Group Specific queries this device has sent out.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGAndSQueriesSen.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGAndSQueriesSent
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGAndSQueriesSen.description: The number of Group and Source specific queries the device has sent out.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1QueriesRcvd.description: The number of version 1 queries received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV2QueriesRcvd.description: The number of version 2 queries received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3QueriesRcvd.description: The number of version 3 queries received. Will read 0 for MLD.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGSQueriesRcvd.description: The number of group specific queries received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGAndSQueriesRcv.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGAndSQueriesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumGAndSQueriesRcv.description: The number of group and source specific queries received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumWrongVersionQue.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumWrongVersionQueriesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumWrongVersionQue.description: The number of queries with the wrong version this device has seen from the network.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1ReportsRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1ReportsRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV1ReportsRcvd.description: The number of version 1 reports this device has received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV2ReportsRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV2ReportsRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV2ReportsRcvd.description: The number of version 2 reports this device has received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3ReportsRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3ReportsRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumV3ReportsRcvd.description: The number of version 3 reports this device has received. This will read 0 for MLD.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumLeavesRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumLeavesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumLeavesRcvd.description: The number of IGMP version 1 or 2 leaves this device has received. Number of MLD version 1 dones this device has received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumBadFramesRcvd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumBadFramesRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumBadFramesRcvd.description: The number of frames deemed received with errors.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsClear.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsClear
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsClear.description: A mechanism to clear the various counters maintained by the IGMP snooping application. Setting the value to true will clear the counters. Setting the value to false will have no effect. This value will always read false

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumCurrentStateRec.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumCurrentStateRecRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumCurrentStateRec.description: The number of current state records this device has received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumFilterModeChang.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumFilterModeChangeRecRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumFilterModeChang.description: The number of filter mode change records this device has received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumSrcListChgRecRc.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumSrcListChgRecRcvd
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsNumSrcListChgRecRc.description: The number of source list change records this device has received.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToInvalidS.description: The number of packets dropped due to receiving an invalid src IP in a frame.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBeingDis.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBeingDisabled

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadHdrLe.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadHdrLength
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadHdrLe.description: The number of packets dropped due to receiving a bad header length.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadIPHdr.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadIPHdrChksm
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadIPHdr.description: The number of packets dropped due to receiving a bad IP header checksum.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadIGMPH.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadIGMPHdrChksm
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadIGMPH.description: The number of packets dropped due to receiving a bad IGMP/MLD header checksum.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToMissingR.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToMissingRtrAlert
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToMissingR.description: The number of packets dropped due to receiving an IGMP/MLD protocol packet missing the router-alert option.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToOffNetwo.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToOffNetworkSrcIP
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToOffNetwo.description: The number of packets dropped due to receiving an off network source IP address.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToZeroSipI.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToZeroSipIPQuery
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToZeroSipI.description: The number of query packets dropped due to having a 0.0.0.0 or 0::0 source IP address.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadGrpAd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadGrpAddressInQuery
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBadGrpAd.description: The number of queries dropped due to bad group address.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToBadGrpAdd.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToBadGrpAddressInLeave
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToBadGrpAdd.description: The number of leaves/dones dropped due to bad group address.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToTooManySr.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToTooManySrcsInQuery
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToTooManySr.description: Number of received queries that have greater than 64 sources. All sources greater than 64 will not be processed.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToMLDQueryF.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToMLDQueryFromNonLinkLocal
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropDueToMLDQueryF.description: Number of MLD queries dropped due to not having a link local source address.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDroppedLeaveWeAreI.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDroppedLeaveWeAreInV1Mode
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDroppedLeaveWeAreI.description: Number of IGMP leaves dropped due to interface being in IGMPv1 mode.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBeingInS.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBeingInSSMRange
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsDueToBeingInS.description: Number of packets dropped due to addresses being in SSM range.

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsProtocolTTLNo.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsProtocolTTLNot1
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropsProtocolTTLNo.description: Number of protocol packets dropped due to having a TTL not equal to 1

etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropReportsDueToTo.name: etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropReportsDueToTooManySrcs
etsysMgmdExtStatsCntrsDropReportsDueToTo.description: Number of IGMPv3/MLDv2 reports dropped due to having greater than 64 source addresses. All sources after 64 are dropped.

etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassificationTable.name: etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassificationTable
etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassificationTable.description: This table contains a listing of how MGMD will classify received IP protocol frames. For example, for a UDP multicast frame received which is IP type 17, MGMD can classify that frame in one of three ways. It can be classified as a multicast data frame, a routing protocol, or it can be ignored. A user may have a need to multicast TCP frames, but still want to send them ONLY to MGMD clients. To do this one would set protocol id 6(TCP) to 'multicastData'

etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassificationEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassificationEntry
etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassificationEntry.description: An entry representing the binding of IP protocol id, to the IGMP classification of a received frame.

etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassification.name: etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassification
etsysMgmdExtProtocolClassification.description: The classification of this protocol id. 1 - Classify as multicast data frame. 2 - Classify as a routing protocol. 3 - Classify as Ignore.

etsysMgmdExtProtocolIdentifier.name: etsysMgmdExtProtocolIdentifier
etsysMgmdExtProtocolIdentifier.description: The set of IP protocol ids to apply the classification to. Example: If this set has protocols(bits) 1 and 5 set to a '1', and the classification is 'multicastData', this will force IGMP to treat received frames with IP protocol ids of 1 and 5 as 'multicast data', and forward those frames to IGMP joined clients. Similarly if ids 1 and 5 were set to 'routing protocol' then IGMP would treat received frames with these ids as routing protocols, etc.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterTable.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterTable
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterTable.description: This table contains paramaters that specify what IGMP/MLD will do with received frames, either flows or protocol.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterEntry.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterEntry
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a filter entry that IGMP/MLD will act upon.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterApplication.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterApplication
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterApplication.description: The multicast application this object refers to. ipv4(1) refers to IGMP, ipv6(2) refers to MLD.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterId.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterId
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterId.description: The input filter index to modify.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterRuleId.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterRuleId
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterRuleId.description: The the rule index to modify for the given filter id.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterStartIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterStartIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterStartIPAddress.description: The staring IP address for this input filter.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterEndIPAddress.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterEndIPAddress
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterEndIPAddress.description: The ending IP address for this input filter.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterProtocolAction.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterProtocolAction
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterProtocolAction.description: The action to perform for any protocol frame with destination IP falling in the range of startIP to end IP. Refer to the MGMDInputFilterProtocolActionsTc textual convention.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterFlowAction.name: etsysMgmdExtInputFilterFlowAction
etsysMgmdExtInputFilterFlowAction.description: The action to perfom for any multicast flow with a destination IP falling in the range of startIP to endIP. Refer to the MGMDInputFilterFlowActionsTc textual convention.

etsysMgmdExtInputFilterRowStatus.description: active(1) creates a filter entry. destroy(6) clears a filter entry.

etsysMgmdExtReadBaseGroup.description: The read MGMD data that must be supported.

etsysMgmdExtWriteBaseGroup.name: etsysMgmdExtWriteBaseGroup
etsysMgmdExtWriteBaseGroup.description: The write MGMD data that must be supported.

etsysMgmdExtReadBaseGroup2.description: The read MGMD data that must be supported.

etsysMgmdExtWriteBaseGroup2.name: etsysMgmdExtWriteBaseGroup2
etsysMgmdExtWriteBaseGroup2.description: The write MGMD data that must be supported.

etsysMgmdExtWriteCompliance.name: etsysMgmdExtWriteCompliance
etsysMgmdExtWriteCompliance.description: The compliance statement for device that support writes to the etsysMgmdExt MIB.

etsysMgmdExtReadCompliance2.name: etsysMgmdExtReadCompliance2
etsysMgmdExtReadCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for devices that support reads from the etsysMgmdExt MIB.
